The paper proposes a novel end-to-end approach for image dehazing, which involves optimizing the generator using a discriminator network and a loss function that evaluates segmentation quality of dehazed images. This approach is inspired by the success of Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN). Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as GANs and loss functions, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves graphics-related tasks such as image segmentation, which falls under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which are commonly used in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
